In English, that's a little awkward to ask. But in Laos, ""Muan baw?"" which means ""Are you happy?"" is a common thing to say.

Would you be delighted to visit Laos one day? 🇱🇦

3 cool facts to know about Karlovy Vary, Czech Republic 🇨🇿 👇

👑 The city is named after its founder, Charles IV, a Holy Roman Emperor and King of Bohemia.

🥯 It is the birthplace of the Carlsbad spa wafers or Karlovarské oplatky––a famous Czech local dessert.

💧 It is known as a ""spa city"" because of its wealth of relaxing hot springs.

I'll give you 3 guesses as to what this is...

A weapon? A fishing rod? Nope!

It's actually an instrument—a single-string musical bow called a berimbau.

It's played by tapping the steel string with a stick called the "baqueta" and by shaking a wicker basket rattle referred to as the "caxixi". The hollowed gourd attached to it can also be opened and closed to modify pitch.

The berimbau is used in Brazil as an instrumental and rhythmic accompaniment to capoeira – a famous Brazilian martial art. 🇧🇷 🪘

What other local musical instruments do you know of?

Have you ever heard of Timkat?

Translating to "baptism" in Amharic, Timkat is one of the oldest religious festivals in Ethiopia. It celebrates the baptism of Jesus Christ through a vibrant, ritualistic procession, song, dance, and prayer.

Timkat is an annual celebration that takes place on the 19th of January. If you plan on visiting Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, sometime soon, this is an event you shouldn't miss! 🇪🇹

Today we honor the life of Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. As we reflect on his legacy, especially in turbulent times like these, we must remember his words and “keep moving.” 

Despite facing many obstacles, it was Dr. King’s perseverance that paved much of the way for the progress we have made. 

Dr. King forever changed the U.S. and inspired others around the world. Here, we see him and his wife Coretta on a 1959 trip to India, which he described as a “pilgrimage.” 

The Kings were greeted with an outpouring of support from India’s leaders and people who admired Dr. King’s work during the Civil Rights Movement.

 Though much was accomplished, we know there is still work to be done. ❤️✨

@cjthe3rd is the principal reason FLY BROTHER (the TV series) exists at all. 

Back in the early aughts, he was co-owner of the startup cable network that originally commissioned the show, based on my travel blog (which still exists, btw). I didn’t want to do it, but he enrolled me in the possibilities. He eventually left cable and we eventually found a home on Public Television and @createtvchannel. 🙏🏾🚀✨

Chester and I have known each other since freshman year at @famu_1887 (way back in the 1900s), but it is an honor, privilege, and blessing to consider him a friend, mentor, and co-creator decades later. Yes, decades.

This is the power of friendship, connection, collaboration, and culture creation. This is Black Excellence. 

This is what so many are, still, so afraid of–because they can’t conceive of what it means to be supported and supportive, loved and loving. So we show them, time and time again.

This is why we celebrate Black History, Present, and Future 365. 🖤

And to our very first funders (after my parents): @drtravel911, @denisewbarreto, and the DAWA Angels Investment Group—all Black women—thank you for believing in me, for choosing me, for loving me. For loving us. 🙏🏾❤️✨
